# cpmtools diskdef for the Teleram T-4000 internal bubble memory image.
#
# Derived from bubble.bin (128 KB):
#   total 1024 x 128-byte sectors; directory at sector 120 (0x3C00);
#   1 KB blocks (113 data blocks, DSM=112); 64 directory entries.
#
# The image was dumped by BUBDUMP in CP/M *logical* sector order (it used the
# BIOS SECTRAN skew table while reading), so it is already de-skewed:
# use "skew 1" (identity) here.
#
# Note: with skew 1, the exact tracks/sectrk split is cosmetic for cpmtools as
# long as sectrk*tracks = 1024 and boottrk*sectrk = 120 (the reserved offset).
# Adjust sectrk/tracks/boottrk to mirror what INFO reports if you like.

diskdef teleram
  seclen 128
  sectrk 8
  tracks 128
  blocksize 1024
  maxdir 64
  boottrk 15
  skew 1
  os 2.2
end
